    public interface ILazyDataset
extends java.io.Serializable, IMetadataProvider, INameable
    This interface defines the lazy parts of a dataset. A dataset is a N-dimensional array of items where N can be zero to represent a zero-rank or single-valued dataset. A zero-rank dataset has an empty array for shape. An item comprises a number of elements.

      • getTransposedView

        ILazyDataset getTransposedView(int... axes)
        Permute copy of dataset's axes so that given order is old order: 
          axisPerm = (p(0), p(1),...) => newdata(n(0), n(1),...) = olddata(o(0), o(1), ...)
  such that n(i) = o(p(i)) for all i
        I.e. for a 3D dataset (1,0,2) implies the new dataset has its 1st dimension running along the old dataset's 2nd dimension and the new 2nd is the old 1st. The 3rd dimension is left unchanged.
        Parameters:
        axes - if zero length then axes order reversed
        Returns:
        remapped view of data
